title: For Sale:  Taurus 9 shot DAO .17M2 snubnose revolver
postcontent:
WITHDRAWN . . . back in the safe.

NOTE:  This is the 9-shot .17 Mach 2 version, not the 17 HMR version, but Armslist did not have 17M2 as a caliber choice.

This is my third and final time posting this.  I've raised the money needed to repair my car so no longer desperate to sell.  I've had a lot of interest from serious buyers in other states, but I have neither the time nor inclination to deal with the hassle and expense of shipping a firearm to an out of state FFL.  I have zero interest in trading for anything: guns, laptops, tattoos, dental work, your roommate's iguana, or whatever.  $300 CASH takes it.  And by CASH I mean no checks or PayPal.  If it does not sell by Monday I'm keeping it.  Great ladies gun with the traditional low profile pearl grips which fit small hands perfectly (original rubber boot grips also included).  

This is a fairly obscure piece, a Taurus "Instant Backup" IB-17 chambered in .17 Mach2, which is a bottlenecked .22LR that fires a jacketed .17 caliber V-MAX projectile at high velocity, with a 9-round cylinder. Factory bobbed hammer, double-action-only.  1.75" barrel, 22 ounces.     

This revolver is a great choice for anyone who is unduly sensitive to recoil, or for situations where overpenetration is a factor. It has solid lockup and perfect timing.  Zero recoil, low noise, very reliable, light trigger pull for a rimfire revolver.  Very unique revolver utilizing a small, bottlenecked cartridge firing tiny jacketed ballistic tipped projectiles at approximately 1,100 fps out of the snub barrel.  9 shots as fast as you can pull the trigger.  Zero problems extracting spent casings.  I took down the forcing cone about a hundreth of an inch with emory cloth so it can go longer between cleanings (tolerances were so tight it needed to be cleaned every third cylinder, now it will go through a box of 50 rounds no problem).  Very accurate revolver within 30 feet (have not tried past that distance).  Should be cleaned after each range session.  If the trigger pull starts to get heavier, it needs a quick cleaning.  This is normal with all DA rimfire revolvers.       

Revolver is in Excellent condition. VERY nice shape, almost like new. Comes with MANY EXTRAS: 200 rounds of V-MAX ammo, Snap-Caps for dry fire practice, a set of vintage Ajax pearl grips (in addition to the stock rubber grips), a .17 caliber bore brush, and the original plastic carry case (with manual, paperwork, etc). Does not come with a holster, but any S&W J-frame holster will fit it perfectly.  I recommend the DeSantis Nemesis pocket holster, which can be found on eBay or Amazon for about 25 bucks.

This is a great little revolver, but need to replace the timing belt (and several other parts) on my car and that takes priority.  This is a GREAT deal for only 300 bucks . . . I paid 400 for the gun and 50 for the grips.

I reserve the right to withdraw this item from sale at any time, or to refuse to deal with anyone I don't like. Will not travel too far from Denver.  Price is FIRM.  Will not ship.  CASH ONLY. Thanks.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Russian Makarov .380
postcontent:
The Russian Makarov .380

The Russian-made Baikal IJ-70 pistol is often referred to simply as the Makarov. Imported by B-West Imports.  The pistol was designed by Nikolay Fyodorovich Makarov in 1948 as a means to firing the more powerful 9 x 18mm round. This gun became the standard Soviet Union military & police sidearm from 1951 - 1991. Presently, the Russian-made IJ-70 is not being imported into the U.S., having been discontinued in 1996, which is what makes this particular firearm so unique.

This Makarov is in nearly perfect condition. Firing pin and bore are bright and clean as well as all finishes on the pistol.  Gun shoots a .380 ACP round, and has a barrel of 3 1/2 inches.  It is double action and has adjustable sights.

Firearm comes with a leather holster, 4 magazines, 2 cleaning tools and manual.
